deo%20app.%20He%20also%20runs%20Threads%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthreads-launch-meta-instagram-twitter-rival-mark-zuckerberg-elon-musk-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Twitter%20clone%20the%20company%20launched%20two%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnofficially%2C%20he's%20become%20one%20of%20Meta's%20chief%20explainers%2C%20frequently%20jumping%20on%20social%20media%20to%20defend%20and%20proselytize%20on%20behalf%20of%20his%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20I%20got%20a%20chance%20to%20interview%20Mosseri%2C%20I%20had%20a%20long%20list%20of%20questions%20about%E2%80%A6%20lots%20of%20things%3A%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20how%20Mosseri%20felt%20about%20the%20company's%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-donald-trump-moderation-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epivot%20to%20Trump-friendly%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-exec-mosseri-tiktok-hurt-youtube-more-than-his-app-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20he%20looked%20at%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20million%20other%20things.%20I%20didn't%20have%20enough%20time%20to%20get%20to%20everything%2C%20but%20I%20got%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20it%2C%20and%20you%20can%20hear%20our%20whole%20conversation%20on%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fchannels-with-peter-kafka%2Fid1080467174%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChannels%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20edited%20excerpt%20below%2C%20Mosseri%20and%20I%20go%20over%20some%20big-picture%20stuff%20that%20tells%20you%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20current%20state%20of%20social%20media%3A%20Like%20why%20Instagram%2C%20Facebook%20and%20every%20other%20social%20media%20platform%20rely%20on%20algorithms%20to%20show%20you%20stuff%20they%20thinks%20you%20like%2C%20instead%20of%20relying%20on%20users%20to%20program%20their%20own%20experience.%20And%20why%20the%20company%20is%20gung-ho%20on%20getting%20users%20to%20privately%20send%20each%20other%20photos%20and%20videos%2C%20instead%20of%20its%20initial%20focus%20%E2%80%94%20getting%20them%20to%20post%20stuff%20on%20a%20public%20feed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20know%20about%20the%20backstory%20behind%20Threads%20%E2%80%94%20the%20text-based%20social%20network%20it%20launched%20just%20as%20Elon%20Musk%20was%20taking%20over%20Twitter.%20Mosseri%20was%20happy%20to%20talk%20about%20all%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeter%20Kafka%3A%20In%20the%20first%20few%20years%20of%20social%20media%20feeds%2C%20users%20would%20see%20a%20list%20of%20everything%20that%20everyone%20they%20were%20following%20had%20posted%2C%20in%20chronological%20order.%20Now%2C%20the%20standard%20at%20every%20app%20is%20a%20curated%2C%20algorithmic%20feed.%20Why%20does%20everyone%20who%20runs%20a%20social%20media%20product%20think%20that's%20better%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdam%20Mosseri%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It's%20because%20it's%20the%20only%20way%20to%20grow%20these%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20amount%20of%20content%20people%20post%20publicly%20in%20feeds%20is%20going%20down%20across%20the%20entire%20industry%2C%20because%20people%20are%20moving%20more%20and%20more%20sharing%20to%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20which%20you%20could%20argue%20is%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20feed%20%E2%80%94%20but%20even%20more%20into%20messaging%2C%20group%20chats%2C%20one-on-one%20chats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Instagram%2C%20there%20are%20way%20more%20photos%20and%20videos%20shared%20into%20DMs%20than%20into%20stories%2C%20and%20way%20more%20photos%20and%20videos%20are%20shared%20into%20stories%20than%20into%20the%20feed.%20So%20if%20the%20amount%20of%20content%20you%20have%20to%20rank%20is%20decreasing%20%E2%80%94%20how%20engaging%20the%20feed%20is%20is%20also%20just%20decreasing.%20It's%20just%20getting%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20show%20recommendations%20because%20you%20might%20follow%20200%20accounts%20and%20one%20in%2010%20of%20them%20posted.%20So%20we've%20%5Bonly%5D%20got%2020%20things%20%5Bto%20show%20you%5D.%20And%20we%20can%20reorder%20those%2020%20things%2020%20factorial%20ways%2C%20but%20that's%20only%20so%20much%20upside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%20if%20we%20look%20at%20the%20billion%20things%20posted%20in%20a%20given%20day%20and%20we%20find%20something%20you're%20interested%20in%2C%20there's%20more%20upside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-instagram-meme-empire-doing-things-strategy-dms-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInstagram%20has%20been%20encouraging%20messaging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%20It's%20something%20you've%20been%20talking%20about%20for%20a%20while.%20It's%20something%20users%20were%20doing%20on%20their%20own%2C%20and%20now%20you%20guys%20are%20responding%20to%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOh%20yeah.%20It's%20a%20paradigm%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20thing%20you%20hear%20is%20that%20people%20are%20going%20to%20chats%20because%20they%20feel%20like%20that's%20safer%20or%20they%20can%20have%20more%20candor.%20But%20are%20regular%20people%20literally%20thinking%20about%20how%20their%20posts%20are%20gonna%20be%20received%3F%20Is%20there%20some%20other%20reason%20people%20are%20sharing%20more%20privately%20versus%20publicly%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20foundational%20reason%20is%20that%20there%20are%20more%20things%20that%20you%20would%20feel%20comfortable%20saying%20to%20somebody%20one-on-one%20than%20things%20you%20would%20feel%20comfortable%20sharing%20publicly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20weirdly%20sad%20example%2C%20but%20you%20could%20think%20of%20sharing%20in-feed%20as%20standing%20on%20top%20of%20your%20roof%2C%20yelling%20something%20at%20a%20hundred%20people%2C%20and%20hoping%20that%2020%20people%20hear%20it.%20There's%20some%20things%20I%20would%20do%20that%20for.%20But%20the%20average%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20of%20things%20I%20would%20say%20to%20you%20on%20a%20phone%20call%2C%20my%20wife%20on%20a%20phone%20call%2C%20my%20best%20friend%20on%20a%20phone%20call%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20of%20those%20things.%20I%20think%20that's%20the%20most%20important%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20that%20shift%20affect%20the%20business%20of%20Meta%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20moves%20more%20and%20more%20of%20that%20friend%20content%20into%20private%20experiences.%20And%20then%20the%20question%20is%2C%20can%20you%20either%20make%20those%20private%20sharing%20experiences%20symbiotic%20with%20the%20ones%20that%20we%20monetize%20%E2%80%94%20like%20feed%20and%20stories%3F%20Or%20can%20you%20monetize%20those%20experiences%20directly%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Instagram%2C%20the%20thing%20that%20has%20been%20amazing%20is%20that%20we%20have%20leaned%20into%20video%20in%20a%20way%20that%20actually%20grows%20messaging.%20When%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20Facebook%20app%2C%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPivot_to_video%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleaned%20a%20lot%20into%20video%20in%202014%2C%2015%2C%2016%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20were%20very%20focused%20on%20trying%20to%20catch%20up%20with%20YouTube%2C%20and%20growing%20video%20grew%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20spent%20in%20the%20Facebook%20app%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20decreased%20everything%20else.%20It%20decreased%20messages%2C%20comments%2C%20likes%2C%20and%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20because%20there's%20less%20ads%20per%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%5BBut%5D%20with%20Reels%20on%20Instagram%2C%20because%20they're%20short%20and%20because%20they're%20entertaining%E2%80%A6%20I'll%20see%20a%20standup%20comic%20doing%20a%20bit%20that%20I%20love%20and%20I'll%20send%20it%20to%20my%20brother%2C%20because%20I%20know%20he's%20going%20to%20enjoy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20I'll%20see%20a%20piece%20on%20politics%20and%20I'll%20send%20it%20to%20you.%20Because%20I%20think%20you%20might%20be%20interested%20in%20it.%20And%20then%20you%20and%20I%20talk%2C%20maybe%20you%20look%20at%20your%20feed%2C%20maybe%20you%20engage%20with%20something%20else.%20Maybe%20you%20send%20that%20to%20somebody%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20there%20is%20a%20private%20messaging%20part%20of%20the%20experience%2C%20%5Bbut%5D%20we've%20managed%20to%20build%20it%20in%20a%20way%20that's%20very%20symbiotic%20with%20the%20public%20context%20%E2%80%94%20like%20feed%20and%20stories%20and%20reels%2C%20which%20we%20monetize%20directly%20with%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe're%20going%20to%20show%20you%20engaging%20stuff%2C%20you're%20going%20engage%20in%20it%2C%20and%20we'll%20be%20able%20to%20monetize%20your%20eyeballs%20like%20we%20always%20have%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20you'll%20share%20it%20with%20other%20people.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20positive%20feedback%20loop.%20And%20it's%20important%20particularly%20for%20Instagram%20because%20we%20are%20about%20connecting%20with%20your%20friends%20over%20creative%20things.%20I%20mean%2C%20for%20some%20people%2C%20we%20might%20be%20a%20pure%20entertainment-based%20or%20public%20content-based%20app.%20But%20we%20want%20friend%20content%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20core%20part%20of%20the%20experience%20for%20most%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20allows%20Instagram%20to%20stay%20social%2C%20but%20still%20grow%20as%20a%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wanted%20to%20ask%20you%20about%20the%20Threads%20origin%20story.%20I%20didn't%20realize%20that%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2Fnews%2F663390%2Fthreads-app-inside-instagram-mosseri%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eit%20was%20originally%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20feature%20within%20Instagram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20talking%20about%20different%20ways%20to%20compete%20more%20directly%20with%20Twitter%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%3F%20I%20know%20that%20back%20around%202010%2C%20the%20two%20services%20were%20fiercely%20competitive.%20And%20then%20basically%20that%20competition%20stopped%2C%20because%20you%20guys%20just%20lapped%20Twitter%20over%20and%20over%20and%20you%20won.%20There%20were%20many%20more%20people%20who%20wanted%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram-like%20experience%20than%20they%20did%20on%20Twitter.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20why%20bother%20going%20back%20to%20Twitter%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20Twitter's%20a%20great%20app%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20ways.%20I%20use%20Twitter%20a%20lot%2C%20still.%20I%20think%20it's%20better%20for%20public%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20it's%20not%20the%20biggest%20app%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20cultural%20relevance.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20really%20vibrant%2C%20amazing%20communities%20there%20%E2%80%94%20NBA%20Twitter%2C%20black%20Twitter%20there.%20There's%20these%20insular%20networks%20like%20VC%20Twitter%20and%20crypto%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20part%20of%20what%20we%20care%20about%20at%20Instagram%20is%20being%20a%20place%20where%20creatives%20do%20their%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20the%20initial%20thought%20was%20to%20bolt%20it%20onto%20Instagram%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20that%20time%20we%20really%20accelerated%20our%20work%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niemanlab.org%2F2023%2F11%2Fhow-13-news-publishers-are-using-whatsapp-channels%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebroadcast%20channels%20on%20WhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20on%20Instagram%20and%20on%20Messenger%20%E2%80%94%20which%20by%20the%20way%2C%20are%20a%20big%20deal%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20particularly%20popularized%20by%20Telegram.%20We%20looked%20at%20and%20had%20a%20bunch%20of%20designs%20for%20building%20something%20like%20Threads%20as%20a%20tab%20into%20Instagram.%20And%20we%20did%20consider%20and%20ended%20up%20building%20a%20separate%20app%2C%20and%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20contentious%20debates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20%3Cem%3Eyou%3C%2Fem%3E%20want%20to%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20did%20you%20want%20what's%20now%20called%20Threads%20to%20live%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20excited%20about%20channels.%20But%20Mark%20%5BZuckerberg%5D%20made%20the%20point%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20agreed%20with%20him%20%E2%80%94%20that%20channels%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20a%20place%20where%20you%20keep%20up%20with%20tons%20and%20tons%20of%20culturally%20relevant%20people.%20They're%20going%20to%20be%20a%20place%20where%20you%20subscribe%20to%20the%20five%20or%2010%20you%20care%20about%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20more%20bullish%20on%20building%20something%20within%20Instagram.%20Mark's%20point%20was%20that%20a%20separate%20app%20will%20be%20harder%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20it%20was%20successful%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20more%20valuable%20thing%20to%20create%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20what%20Mark%20does%20is%20anchor%20us%20really%20high.%20And%20no%20matter%20how%20strong%20a%20year%20we%20have%2C%20the%20question%20is%20always%20%E2%80%94%20how%20can%20we%20do%20better%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20late.%20I%20was%20in%20Italy%20for%20my%20anniversary%20with%20my%20wife%2C%20and%20%5BMark's%5D%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20if%20you%20were%20gonna%20do%20something%20bigger%2C%20what%20would%20you%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20was%20riffing%20and%20I%20kind%20of%20pitched%20a%20version%20of%20Threads%3A%20We'll%20lean%20on%20Instagram's%20strength%20with%20creators.%20We'll%20use%20Instagram%20identity.%20You%20can%20bootstrap%20it%20with%20%5BInstragram's%20social%5D%20graph%2C%20but%20we'll%20focus%20on%20basic%20replies%20and%20threads.%20I%20called%20it%20Textagram%20as%20a%20joke.%20Which%20unfortunately%20stuck%20as%20a%